msgstr "豁免过时的自动化；已接受但被阻塞的工作"

#: src/maintainers/labels.md:181
msgid "Maintenance triggers"
msgstr "维护触发器"

#: src/maintainers/labels.md:183
msgid "Update this page when:"
msgstr "在以下情况时更新此页面："

#: src/maintainers/labels.md:185
msgid ""
"A new channel, provider, or tool is added to the source tree (path labels "
"need new entries)."
msgstr "向源代码树中添加了新的通道、提供程序或工具（路径标签需要新增条目）。"

#: src/maintainers/labels.md:186
msgid "A label policy or threshold changes."
msgstr "标签策略或阈值已更改。"

#: src/maintainers/labels.md:187
msgid "A new triage workflow surfaces or an old one is removed."
msgstr "新的分诊工作流出现，或旧的被移除。"

#: src/maintainers/labels.md:189
msgid ""
"The automation status notes (\"currently applied manually\") are "
"deliberately included so a future maintainer doesn't assume the absence of a "
"workflow means the label tier doesn't exist."
msgstr "自动化状态备注（“目前手动应用”）被特意包含在内，以便未来的维护者不会误以为工作流的缺失意味着标签层级不存在。"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:3
msgid ""
"When a maintainer-authored PR replaces a contributor's open PR, attribution "
"and process discipline keep the contributor relationship healthy. This page "
"is the rulebook."
msgstr "当维护者提交的 PR 替换了贡献者的开放 PR 时，归属关系和流程纪律有助于保持贡献者关系的健康。本页面是规则手册。"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:5
msgid "Try the alternatives first"
msgstr "先尝试其他替代方案"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:7
msgid ""
"Superseding is the heaviest option. Before you open one, try in this order:"
msgstr "Superseding 是最重的选项。在打开它之前，请按以下顺序尝试："

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:9
msgid ""
"**Push fixups to the contributor's branch.** If the PR has "
"`maintainerCanModify: true` (the default for PRs from personal forks — "
"confirm with `gh pr view <number> --json maintainerCanModify`), push your "
"fixups directly and merge the contributor's PR. Attribution stays clean in "
"`git log`, `git blame`, and the contributor's GitHub profile. Coordinate "
"with the contributor first if your fix isn't trivial — pushing while they "
"have unpushed work creates conflicts they have to resolve."
msgstr "**将修复提交推送到贡献者的分支。** 如果 PR 具有 `maintainerCanModify: true`（来自个人 fork 的 PR 的默认值 — 可通过 `gh pr view <number> --json maintainerCanModify` 确认），则直接推送你的修复提交并合并贡献者的 PR。`git log`、`git blame` 以及贡献者的 GitHub 个人资料中的署名将保持清晰。如果你的修复并非微不足道，请先与贡献者协调 — 在他们有未推送的更改时推送会导致他们需要解决的冲突。"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:11
msgid ""
"**Leave a review with specific requested changes.** If the contributor is "
"responsive and the fix is within their original scope (a clippy lint, an "
"edge case, a test addition), request the change and let them push the fixup. "
"Single-line fixes are almost always better as a requested change than a "
"supersede."
msgstr "**提出包含具体所需更改的审查意见。** 如果贡献者响应积极，且修复内容在其原始范围内（例如 clippy 警告、边界情况、测试用例添加），请提出更改请求，并让他们推送修复提交。单行修复几乎总是比覆盖提交更适合作为更改请求。"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:13
msgid ""
"**Open a follow-up PR after merging.** If the contributor's PR is correct as-"
"is and you want additional hardening, merge first, then open a separate PR. "
"Attribution preserved; the cost is a brief window with known issues on "
"`master`."
msgstr "**合并后提交一个后续 PR。** 如果贡献者的 PR 本身是正确的，而你希望进一步加固代码，请先合并该 PR，然后再提交一个单独的 PR。贡献者署名得以保留；代价是 `master` 分支上会短暂存在已知问题。"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:15
msgid "Supersede only when one of these applies:"
msgstr "仅在以下情况之一适用时，才进行替代："

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:17
msgid ""
"The contributor is unresponsive (no reply within the project's review SLA)."
msgstr "贡献者未响应（在项目审查 SLA 内无回复）。"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:18
msgid ""
"The change requires substantially more work than the contributor's original "
"scope."
msgstr "该变更需要的工作量远超贡献者最初的范围。"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:19
msgid ""
"Multiple related contributor PRs need to be unified into a single coherent "
"change."
msgstr "多个相关的贡献者 PR 需要合并为一个连贯的变更。"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:20
msgid ""
"The contributor opted out of maintainer edits (`maintainerCanModify: false`) "
"and a follow-up PR is impractical."
msgstr "贡献者选择不接受维护者编辑（`maintainerCanModify: false`），且后续 PR 不切实际。"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:22
msgid "Attribution rules"
msgstr "归属规则"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:24
msgid ""
"When you do supersede and you carry forward substantive code or design "
"decisions, preserve authorship explicitly:"
msgstr "当你进行替代（supersede）并延续实质性的代码或设计决策时，请明确保留作者信息："

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:26
msgid ""
"Add one `Co-authored-by: Name <email>` trailer per superseded contributor "
"whose work was materially incorporated. Use a GitHub-recognized email — "
"either the contributor's `<login@users.noreply.github.com>` form or their "
"verified commit email."
msgstr "为每个其工作被实质性合并的已替代贡献者添加一个 `Co-authored-by: Name <email>` 尾注。使用 GitHub 认可的邮箱——可以是贡献者的 `<login@users.noreply.github.com>` 格式，也可以是他们的已验证提交邮箱。"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:27
msgid ""
"Trailers go on their own lines after a blank line at the end of the commit "
"message. Never encode them as escaped `\\n` text."
msgstr "trailers 应位于提交消息末尾的空白行之后的单独行上。切勿将其编码为转义的 `\\n` 文本。"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:28
msgid ""
"In the PR body, list the superseded PR links and briefly state what was "
"incorporated from each."
msgstr "在 PR 正文中，列出被取代的 PR 链接，并简要说明从每个 PR 中合并了哪些内容。"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:29
msgid ""
"If no actual code or design was incorporated (only inspiration), don't use "
"`Co-authored-by` — give credit in the PR notes section instead."
msgstr "如果没有实际代码或设计被纳入（仅作为灵感），请勿使用 `Co-authored-by`，而是在 PR 备注部分给予致谢。"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:31
msgid ""
"These trailers route GitHub's contributor recognition correctly. Without "
"them, the original author shows up as \"Closed\" on their PR with no record "
"of the carry-forward."
msgstr "这些 trailer 能正确路由 GitHub 的贡献者识别信息。如果没有它们，原始作者在其 PR 上会显示为“已关闭”，且没有保留后续贡献的记录。"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:33
msgid "PR title and body template"
msgstr "PR 标题和正文模板"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:65
msgid "Commit message template"
msgstr "提交消息模板"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:84
msgid "Closing the superseded PRs"
msgstr "关闭已废弃的 PR"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:86
msgid "Close each with a comment that names the new PR and the carry-forward:"
msgstr "在每个末尾添加注释，注明新的 PR 和延续内容："

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:94
msgid ""
"If the contributor pushed back on a particular design choice during their "
"original PR and the supersede took a different direction, name that "
"explicitly. Don't pretend it's a clean carry-forward when it's actually a "
"redesign."
msgstr "如果贡献者在原始 PR 中对某个设计选择提出了异议，而后续版本采取了不同的方向，请明确指出这一点。不要将其伪装成干净的延续，而实际上却是重新设计。"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:96
msgid "Handoff template (agent → agent or agent → maintainer)"
msgstr "交接模板（代理 → 代理 或 代理 → 维护者）"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:98
msgid "When handing off mid-flight work, include:"
msgstr "在进行中途工作交接时，请包括以下内容："

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:100
msgid "**What changed.**"
msgstr "**变更内容。**"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:101
msgid "**What did not change.**"
msgstr "**未更改的内容。**"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:102
msgid "**Validation run and results.**"
msgstr "**验证运行及结果。**"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:103
msgid "**Remaining risks / unknowns.**"
msgstr "**剩余风险/未知项。**"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:104
msgid "**Next recommended action.**"
msgstr "**下一步推荐操作。**"

#: src/maintainers/superseding.md:106
msgid ""
"This applies to supersedes that span multiple work sessions, agent-assisted "
"handovers between maintainers, and any case where one person needs to pick "
"up another's in-progress branch."
msgstr "这适用于跨越多个工作会话的替代、维护者之间由代理协助的交接，以及任何需要一人接手另一人正在进行的分支的情况。"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:1
msgid "Release Runbook"
msgstr "发布运行手册"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:3
msgid ""
"The standard procedure for cutting a stable release. Predictable, "
"repeatable, and only ever from `master`."
msgstr "发布稳定版本的标准化流程。可预测、可重复，且仅从 `master` 分支进行。"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:5
msgid "When to release"
msgstr "何时发布"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:7
msgid ""
"**Patch / minor**: weekly or bi-weekly cadence. Don't wait for huge commit "
"batches to accumulate."
msgstr "**补丁/次要版本**：每周或每两周发布一次。不要等待大量提交累积。"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:8
msgid "**Emergency security fixes**: out-of-band, as needed."
msgstr "**紧急安全修复**：按需进行，不遵循常规发布周期。"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:9
msgid "The release pipeline never publishes from a feature branch."
msgstr "发布流水线从不从功能分支发布。"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:11
msgid "Workflow surface"
msgstr "工作流表面"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:13
msgid "Release automation lives in:"
msgstr "发布自动化位于："

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:17
msgid ""
"Full stable release pipeline. Tag-push and `workflow_dispatch` triggers."
msgstr "完整的稳定版本发布流程。通过标签推送和 `workflow_dispatch` 触发。"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:18
msgid ""
"Pushes the updated PKGBUILD to AUR (workflow_call from release; manual "
"dispatch with `dry_run`)."
msgstr "将更新后的 PKGBUILD 推送到 AUR（通过 release 的 workflow_call 触发；使用 `dry_run` 手动调度）。"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:19
msgid "Opens a PR against `Homebrew/homebrew-core` from the bot fork."
msgstr "从机器人分支向 `Homebrew/homebrew-core` 发起一个 PR。"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:20
msgid "Updates the Scoop bucket manifest."
msgstr "更新 Scoop 存储库清单。"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:21
msgid "Posts the release notes to Discord `#releases` after publish."
msgstr "在发布后将发布说明发布到 Discord 的 `#releases` 频道。"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:22
msgid "Posts an announcement tweet."
msgstr "发布一条公告推文。"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:23
msgid "`sync-marketplace-templates.yml`"
msgstr "`sync-marketplace-templates.yml`"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:23
msgid ""
"Updates downstream marketplace templates (Dokploy, EasyPanel) after publish."
msgstr "在发布后更新下游市场模板（Dokploy、EasyPanel）。"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:25
msgid "`release-stable-manual.yml` runs in two modes:"
msgstr "`release-stable-manual.yml` 以两种模式运行："

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:27
msgid "**Tag push** (`v*` tag) — full publish."
msgstr "**标签推送**（`v*` 标签）——完整发布。"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:28
msgid ""
"**Manual dispatch** — verification-only or publish, controlled by "
"`publish_release` input."
msgstr "**手动分发** — 仅验证或发布，由 `publish_release` 输入控制。"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:30
msgid ""
"A weekly schedule also fires the workflow in verification-only mode, so "
"you'll see green CI on `master` even between releases."
msgstr "每周计划还会以仅验证模式触发工作流，因此即使在版本发布之间，你也会在 `master` 分支上看到绿色的 CI 状态。"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:32
msgid "Publish-mode guardrails"
msgstr "发布模式护栏"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:34
msgid "The pipeline refuses to publish unless every guardrail holds:"
msgstr "流水线拒绝发布，除非所有护栏都满足条件："

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:36
msgid "Tag matches semver-like `vX.Y.Z[-suffix]`."
msgstr "标签匹配类似语义化版本 `vX.Y.Z[-后缀]` 的格式。"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:37
msgid "Tag exists on `origin`."
msgstr "标签存在于 `origin` 上。"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:38
msgid "Tag commit is reachable from `origin/master`."
msgstr "标签提交可从 `origin/master` 访问。"

#: src/maintainers/release-runbook.md:39
